          'Stage 3: Government/Defense Contract ($100M to $500M). Military procurement validation is the single largest step-up in the model. When a defense agency signs a contract, it signals that the product has survived rigorous security evaluation, supply chain verification, and operational testing. For PQC companies, defense adoption serves as a de facto certification that no commercial audit can match. The NSA\'s CNSA 2.0 suite mandates ML-KEM adoption for all National Security Systems by 2027. NATO DIANA (Defence Innovation Accelerator for the North Atlantic) actively funds quantum-safe communications. Norway\'s FFI (Forsvarets forskningsinstitutt) has quantum security research programs aligned with the NOK 1.75 billion national quantum initiative announced in August 2025. A contract from any of these entities reprices the company from "promising startup" to "procurement-validated vendor," which unlocks the defense primes (Thales, Raytheon, L3Harris) as channel partners and integration targets.',
